data.enText: the fact of having or expressing opinions that are different from those that are officially accepted

data.chText: 政治观点 / 宗教信仰上的分歧
（诉讼案中某法官对其他法官判决的）异议，不同意见
data.enText: a judge's statement giving reasons why he or she disagrees with a decision made by the other judges in a court case
to have or express opinions that are different from those that are officially accepted

data.chText: 只有两位部长与官方持不同的观点。
data.enText: Only two ministers dissented from the official view.

data.chText: 持不同意见的团体；反对的呼声；不同的观点；异议

simple_means.memory_skill: dis 分离 + sent 感觉 → 感觉有分歧 → 持不同意见

means: (与官方的或诉讼案中某法官对其他法官判决的)不同意见

tr: a public (often organized) manifestation of dissent
(law) the difference of one judge's opinion from that of the majority
example: he expressed his dissent in a contrary opinion
She disagrees with her husband on many questions

tr: express opposition through action or words
example: dissent to the laws of the country

value.def: Dissent is strong disagreement or dissatisfaction with a decision or opinion, especially one that is supported by most people or by people in authority.

example.ex: He is the toughest military ruler yet and has responded harshly to any dissent...
example.tran: 他是迄今最强硬的军事统治者，对任何异议都一律进行打压。

example.ex: Political dissent would no longer be tolerated...
example.tran: 政见不和将不再被容忍。

example.ex: I made a gesture of dissent.
example.tran: 我做了个表示不同意的手势。

value.tran: (尤指与多数人或权威人士的)意见不一致,意见分歧

value.def: If you dissent, you express disagreement with a decision or opinion, especially one that is supported by most people or by people in authority.

example.ex: Just one of the 10 members dissented...
No one dissents from the decision to unify...
example.tran: 没有人反对统一的决定。

example.ex: There are likely to be many dissenting voices.
example.tran: 可能会有很多不赞成的声音。

value.tran: 不同意，持异议(尤指与多数人或权威人士支持的观点、决定相左)
